Vice President Kamala Harris visited Plymouth, New Hampshire to discuss the importance of broadband access, particularly in rural areas. She praised Senator Maggie Hassan for her leadership and advocacy for broadband expansion. Harris highlighted the significance of broadband during the pandemic, such as its role in education, telemedicine, and small businesses. She emphasized that access to broadband should be affordable and accessible for everyone. The American Jobs Plan includes $100 billion to expand broadband access, with a focus on co-ops and nonprofit organizations. Harris commended the work of the Plymouth Area Renewable Energy Initiative (PAREI) in building a broadband network and stressed the importance of federal support for similar initiatives.